{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "Cartes synth\u00e8ses quotidiennes de la couverture de neige et de glace continentale au Canada, 2005-01-03", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Cartes synth\u00e8ses quotidiennes de la couverture de neige et de glace continentale au Canada, 2005-01-03", "data_series_issue_identification": "Daily Canadian Snow and Inland Ice Cover Synthesis Maps, 2005-01-03", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Cartes synth\u00e8ses quotidiennes de la couverture de neige et de glace continentale au Canada", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Ce jeu de donn\u00e9es correspond \u00e0 la carte de couverture de neige et de glace produite un jour plus tard sur le territoire canadien et ses environs. La carte est produite en fusionnant trois cartes de la couverture de neige et de glace d\u00e9j\u00e0 valid\u00e9es fournies par la NOAA, la NASA et Ressources naturelles Canada. Ces cartes sont reconnues individuellement pour leur concordance avec les donn\u00e9es sur le parcours d'enneigement in-situ fournies par le Service m\u00e9t\u00e9orologique du Canada. En principe, on effectue la cartographie d'apr\u00e8s l'image composite MODIS quotidienne \u00e0 r\u00e9solution de 500 m de la couverture nivale. Cependant, les cartes \u00e0 r\u00e9solution 4 km de la NOAA sont utilis\u00e9es pour couvrir les vides dus \u00e0 la pr\u00e9sence de nuages dans l'image composite.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-175, 38], [-175, 90], [-54, 90], [-54, 38], [-175, 38]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Inland Waters  Eaux int\u00e9rieures", "tags": [{"name": "Ice  Glace"}, {"name": "Snow  Neige"}, {"name": "Inland Waters  Eaux int\u00e9rieures"}, {"name": "Oceans  Oc\u00e9an"}, {"name": "Inland water resources  Ressources en eaux int\u00e9rieures"}, {"name": "Oceans  Oc\u00e9an"}, {"name": "Coasts  Littoral"}, {"name": "Earth Sciences  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Cryosphere  Cryosph\u00e8re"}, {"name": "Snowice  Neigeglace"}, {"name": "Snow cover  Couverture de neige"}, {"name": "Snow depth  \u00c9paisseur de neige"}, {"name": "Lake ice  Glace lacustre"}, {"name": "Ice cover continental  Couverture de glace continentale"}, {"name": "Ice  Glace"}, {"name": "Alberta  Alberta"}, {"name": "British Columbia  Colombie-Britannique"}, {"name": "Manitoba  Manitoba"}, {"name": "New Brunswick  Nouveau-Brunswick"}, {"name": "Newfoundland and Labrador  Terre-Neuve-et-Labrador"}, {"name": "Northwest Territories  Territoires du Nord-Ouest"}, {"name": "Nova Scotia  Nouvelle-\u00c9cosse"}, {"name": "Nunavut  Nunavut"}, {"name": "Ontario  Ontario"}, {"name": "Prince Edward Island  \u00cele-du-Prince-\u00c9douard"}, {"name": "Qu\u00e9bec  Qu\u00e9bec"}, {"name": "Saskatchewan  Saskatchewan"}, {"name": "Yukon  Yukon"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2005-01-03", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "Daily Canadian Snow and Inland Ice Cover Synthesis Maps", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "name": "01826885-6bb0-5647-868b-2a7649b48f65", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01826885-6bb0-5647-868b-2a7649b48f65.html", "notes": "This dataset corresponds to a next day map of snow and ice cover over Canada and its surrounding territories. The map is produced by blending three already validation snow and ice cover maps provided by NOAA, NASA and Natural Resources Canada. These maps have already been individually shown to have similar agreement with in-situ snow course data provided by the Meteorological Service of Canada. Nominally, the 500m resolution MODIS snow cover daily composite is mapped. However, NOAA 4km resolution maps are used to fill gaps due to the presence of clouds within that composite.", "title": "Daily Canadian Snow and Inland Ice Cover Synthesis Maps, 2005-01-03", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01826885-6bb0-5647-868b-2a7649b48f65.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Toporama", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "Biannually | Semestriel", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Toporama est un produit num\u00e9rique de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence topographique produit par Ressources naturelles Canada (RNCan). Toporama couvre le territoire canadien et offre une information topographique, g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9e et symbolis\u00e9e en format matriciel. Le d\u00e9coupage, le contenu et la repr\u00e9sentation de ce produit sont similaires \u00e0 celui des cartes topographiques \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle 1/50 000.  Toporama est publi\u00e9 sous forme d'\u00e9dition (\u00ab release \u00bb) selon un intervalle d'environ six mois. Toporama est distribu\u00e9 sans frais par l'entremise du portail G\u00e9oGratis (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) dans le format matriciel GeoTIFF qui est un format matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9. Toporama est disponible dans les syst\u00e8mes de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatial suivants : universel transverse de Mercator (UTM) et g\u00e9ographique (latitude et longitude).  Toporama est un produit destin\u00e9 au grand public pouvant \u00eatre utilis\u00e9 notamment par les utilisateurs de syst\u00e8mes GPS qui ont besoin d'un produit cartographique matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-135, 68.25], [-135, 68.5], [-134, 68.5], [-134, 68.25], [-135, 68.25]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "TOPORAMA107B066.0  TOPORAMA107B066.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Science Keywords BIOSPHERE VEGETATION  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques biosph\u00e8re v\u00e9g\u00e9tation"}, {"name": "Administratives Boundaries  Limites administratives"}, {"name": "Buildings and Structures  B\u00e2timents et structures"}, {"name": "Energy  \u00c9nergie"}, {"name": "Hydrography  Hydrographie"}, {"name": "Industrial and Commercial Areas  Zones industrielles et commerciales"}, {"name": "Places of Interest  Lieux dint\u00e9r\u00eats"}, {"name": "Relief and Landforms  Relief et formes"}, {"name": "ToponymyPlace Names  ToponymieNoms de lieux"}, {"name": "Water Saturated Soils  Sols satur\u00e9s deau"}, {"name": "SCHOONER CHANNEL  SCHOONER CHANNEL"}, {"name": "107B06  107B06"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1950", "data_series_name": "Toporama", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1950", "name": "01829f43-12aa-4a51-b6fc-d6ebd7ae1523", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01829f43-12aa-4a51-b6fc-d6ebd7ae1523.html", "notes": "Toporama is a digital topographic reference product developed by Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). It covers the entire area of Canada's landmass and provides topographic, geo-referenced, and symbolic information in a raster format. The delimitation, content and representation of this product are similar to those of 1:50,000 scale topographical maps.  Toporama is published as an edition (or \"release\") approximately every six months. It is available free of charge through the GeoGratis portal (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) in GeoTIFF format, which is a geo-referenced raster format. Toporama is available in the following spatial reference systems: Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) and geographic (latitude and longitude).  Toporama is a product aimed at the general public that can be used by GPS system users who need a geo-referenced raster map product.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01829f43-12aa-4a51-b6fc-d6ebd7ae1523.html", "department_number": ""}
