{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "Cartes synth\u00e8ses quotidiennes de la couverture de neige et de glace continentale au Canada, 2003-11-11", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Cartes synth\u00e8ses quotidiennes de la couverture de neige et de glace continentale au Canada, 2003-11-11", "data_series_issue_identification": "Daily Canadian Snow and Inland Ice Cover Synthesis Maps, 2003-11-11", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Cartes synth\u00e8ses quotidiennes de la couverture de neige et de glace continentale au Canada", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Ce jeu de donn\u00e9es correspond \u00e0 la carte de couverture de neige et de glace produite un jour plus tard sur le territoire canadien et ses environs. La carte est produite en fusionnant trois cartes de la couverture de neige et de glace d\u00e9j\u00e0 valid\u00e9es fournies par la NOAA, la NASA et Ressources naturelles Canada. Ces cartes sont reconnues individuellement pour leur concordance avec les donn\u00e9es sur le parcours d'enneigement in-situ fournies par le Service m\u00e9t\u00e9orologique du Canada. En principe, on effectue la cartographie d'apr\u00e8s l'image composite MODIS quotidienne \u00e0 r\u00e9solution de 500 m de la couverture nivale. Cependant, les cartes \u00e0 r\u00e9solution 4 km de la NOAA sont utilis\u00e9es pour couvrir les vides dus \u00e0 la pr\u00e9sence de nuages dans l'image composite.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-175, 38], [-175, 90], [-54, 90], [-54, 38], [-175, 38]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Inland Waters  Eaux int\u00e9rieures", "tags": [{"name": "Ice  Glace"}, {"name": "Snow  Neige"}, {"name": "Inland Waters  Eaux int\u00e9rieures"}, {"name": "Oceans  Oc\u00e9an"}, {"name": "Inland water resources  Ressources en eaux int\u00e9rieures"}, {"name": "Oceans  Oc\u00e9an"}, {"name": "Coasts  Littoral"}, {"name": "Earth Sciences  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Cryosphere  Cryosph\u00e8re"}, {"name": "Snowice  Neigeglace"}, {"name": "Snow cover  Couverture de neige"}, {"name": "Snow depth  \u00c9paisseur de neige"}, {"name": "Lake ice  Glace lacustre"}, {"name": "Ice cover continental  Couverture de glace continentale"}, {"name": "Ice  Glace"}, {"name": "Alberta  Alberta"}, {"name": "British Columbia  Colombie-Britannique"}, {"name": "Manitoba  Manitoba"}, {"name": "New Brunswick  Nouveau-Brunswick"}, {"name": "Newfoundland and Labrador  Terre-Neuve-et-Labrador"}, {"name": "Northwest Territories  Territoires du Nord-Ouest"}, {"name": "Nova Scotia  Nouvelle-\u00c9cosse"}, {"name": "Nunavut  Nunavut"}, {"name": "Ontario  Ontario"}, {"name": "Prince Edward Island  \u00cele-du-Prince-\u00c9douard"}, {"name": "Qu\u00e9bec  Qu\u00e9bec"}, {"name": "Saskatchewan  Saskatchewan"}, {"name": "Yukon  Yukon"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2003-11-11", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "Daily Canadian Snow and Inland Ice Cover Synthesis Maps", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "name": "01861087-731b-5bb1-b524-5cb9635f1341", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01861087-731b-5bb1-b524-5cb9635f1341.html", "notes": "This dataset corresponds to a next day map of snow and ice cover over Canada and its surrounding territories. The map is produced by blending three already validation snow and ice cover maps provided by NOAA, NASA and Natural Resources Canada. These maps have already been individually shown to have similar agreement with in-situ snow course data provided by the Meteorological Service of Canada. Nominally, the 500m resolution MODIS snow cover daily composite is mapped. However, NOAA 4km resolution maps are used to fill gaps due to the presence of clouds within that composite.", "title": "Daily Canadian Snow and Inland Ice Cover Synthesis Maps, 2003-11-11", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01861087-731b-5bb1-b524-5cb9635f1341.html", "department_number": ""}
