{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Les fichiers CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer ont \u00e9t\u00e9 produits \u00e0 partir des cartes topographiques publi\u00e9es par le Gouvernement du Canada. Ces fichiers sont bas\u00e9s sur le Syst\u00e8me national de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence cartographique (SNRC) et disponibles aux \u00e9chelles de 1/50 000 et 1/250 000. Chaque fichier ou jeu de donn\u00e9es CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer contient l'ensemble de l'information figurant au recto de la carte topographique. Cela comprend l'information topographique incluse \u00e0 l'int\u00e9rieur de l'orle cartographique de m\u00eame que l'habillage de la carte, soit l'information situ\u00e9e en p\u00e9riph\u00e9rie de l'orle cartographique.  Les donn\u00e9es contenues dans ce fichier CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer proviennent du balayage d'une carte topographique papier monochrome (noir et blanc).  Suite au balayage initial de la carte papier, ce fichier a \u00e9t\u00e9 inspect\u00e9 et class\u00e9 \" Provisoire\". Ce fichier inclut un filigrane \"Impression provisoire\" au bas du coin inf\u00e9rieur gauche de la carte. La qualit\u00e9 des impressions provisoire varie grandement. Un certain nombre d'op\u00e9rations de nettoyage, d\u00e9coupage, mise \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle et ajustement des tons et couleurs peuvent \u00eatre n\u00e9cessaires afin d'am\u00e9liorer la qualit\u00e9 de l'impression.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-95.5, 66.25], [-95.5, 66.5], [-95, 66.5], [-95, 66.25], [-95.5, 66.25]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "CANMATRIX2056L061.0  CANMATRIX2056L061.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "056L06  056L06"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1991", "data_series_name": "CanMatrix - Print Ready", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1991", "name": "018b40d0-8faa-48bd-9c10-db240869faa6", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018b40d0-8faa-48bd-9c10-db240869faa6.html", "notes": "CanMatrix - Print Ready files were produced from topographic maps published by the Government of Canada, and correspond to the National Topographic System (NTS) grid at 1:50 000 and 1:250 000 scales. Each CanMatrix - Print Ready file or dataset contains all of the information shown on the front of the topographic map, including the topographic information within the neatline of the map, and the information in the border of the map outside of the neatline.  This CanMatrix - Print Ready file was produced by scanning a monochrome (black and white) paper topographic map.  Following initial scanning of the paper map, the digital file was inspected and classified as \"Provisional\". This file includes a \"Provisional Print\" watermark in the bottom left corner of the map. The printing quality of Provisional Prints varies greatly. Varying amounts of cleaning, trimming, scaling, and shade/colour adjustment may be required to improve the print quality.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018b40d0-8faa-48bd-9c10-db240869faa6.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.1", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.1", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "CanTopo", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "CanTopo est la nouvelle g\u00e9n\u00e9ration de cartes topographiques produites par Ressources naturelles Canada. Ce produit cartographique num\u00e9rique provient des meilleures sources de donn\u00e9es disponibles couvrant le territoire canadien et offre un produit cartographique de qualit\u00e9 en formats vectoriel et matriciel qui est conforme aux normes g\u00e9omatiques internationales.  CanTopo est un produit de sources multiples g\u00e9n\u00e9r\u00e9 \u00e0 partie de la Base de donn\u00e9es cartographique (BDC) d\u00e9crite dans les Sp\u00e9cifications de produit de la Base de donn\u00e9es cartographiques. Les donn\u00e9es de la BDC proviennent principalement de l'initiative G\u00e9oBase (www.geobase.ca), des donn\u00e9es topographiques num\u00e9riques de Ressources naturelles Canada et de donn\u00e9es d'initiatives nationales. Des donn\u00e9es de sources faisant autorit\u00e9 telles que provenant d'autres agences gouvernementales autant f\u00e9d\u00e9rales que provinciales, sont utilis\u00e9es entrepos\u00e9es et identifi\u00e9es.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-67, 64], [-67, 64.25], [-66.5, 64.25], [-66.5, 64], [-67, 64]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "CANTOPO026B021.0  CANTOPO026B021.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Science Keywords BIOSPHERE VEGETATION  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques biosph\u00e8re v\u00e9g\u00e9tation"}, {"name": "Administratives Boundaries  Limites administratives"}, {"name": "Buildings and Structures  B\u00e2timents et structures"}, {"name": "Energy  \u00c9nergie"}, {"name": "Hydrography  Hydrographie"}, {"name": "Industrial and Commercial Areas  Zones industrielles et commerciales"}, {"name": "Places of Interest  Lieux dint\u00e9r\u00eats"}, {"name": "Relief and Landforms  Relief et formes"}, {"name": "ToponymyPlace Names  ToponymieNoms de lieux"}, {"name": "Water Saturated Soils  Sols satur\u00e9s deau"}, {"name": "026B02  026B02"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1958-08-24", "data_series_name": "CanTopo", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1958-08-24", "name": "018b4ac3-c55e-4409-9433-95f22f1003c8", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018b4ac3-c55e-4409-9433-95f22f1003c8.html", "notes": "CanTopo is the next generation of topographic maps being produced by Natural Resources Canada. This digital cartographic product originates from the best available data sources covering the Canadian territory and offers a quality cartographic product in vector and raster format that complies with international geomatics standards.  CanTopo is a multi-source product generated from the Cartographic Data Base (CDB) described in the Cartographic Data Base (CDB) Product Specification. Data within the CDB comes mainly from the GeoBase initiative (www.geobase.ca), Natural Resources Canada digital topographic data and data from national initiatives. Data from authoritative sources, such as other government agencies both federal and provincial, are identified, stored, and used.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018b4ac3-c55e-4409-9433-95f22f1003c8.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Toporama", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "Biannually | Semestriel", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Toporama est un produit num\u00e9rique de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence topographique produit par Ressources naturelles Canada (RNCan). Toporama couvre le territoire canadien et offre une information topographique, g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9e et symbolis\u00e9e en format matriciel. Le d\u00e9coupage, le contenu et la repr\u00e9sentation de ce produit sont similaires \u00e0 celui des cartes topographiques \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle 1/50 000.  Toporama est publi\u00e9 sous forme d'\u00e9dition (\u00ab release \u00bb) selon un intervalle d'environ six mois. Toporama est distribu\u00e9 sans frais par l'entremise du portail G\u00e9oGratis (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) dans le format matriciel GeoTIFF qui est un format matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9. Toporama est disponible dans les syst\u00e8mes de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatial suivants : universel transverse de Mercator (UTM) et g\u00e9ographique (latitude et longitude).  Toporama est un produit destin\u00e9 au grand public pouvant \u00eatre utilis\u00e9 notamment par les utilisateurs de syst\u00e8mes GPS qui ont besoin d'un produit cartographique matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-90, 66.75], [-90, 67], [-89.5, 67], [-89.5, 66.75], [-90, 66.75]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "TOPORAMA056I135.0  TOPORAMA056I135.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Science Keywords BIOSPHERE VEGETATION  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques biosph\u00e8re v\u00e9g\u00e9tation"}, {"name": "Administratives Boundaries  Limites administratives"}, {"name": "Buildings and Structures  B\u00e2timents et structures"}, {"name": "Energy  \u00c9nergie"}, {"name": "Hydrography  Hydrographie"}, {"name": "Industrial and Commercial Areas  Zones industrielles et commerciales"}, {"name": "Places of Interest  Lieux dint\u00e9r\u00eats"}, {"name": "Relief and Landforms  Relief et formes"}, {"name": "ToponymyPlace Names  ToponymieNoms de lieux"}, {"name": "Water Saturated Soils  Sols satur\u00e9s deau"}, {"name": "056I13  056I13"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1957", "data_series_name": "Toporama", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1957", "name": "018c1f31-1de1-43c9-b4f5-98b1d2f51db3", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018c1f31-1de1-43c9-b4f5-98b1d2f51db3.html", "notes": "Toporama is a digital topographic reference product developed by Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). It covers the entire area of Canada's landmass and provides topographic, geo-referenced, and symbolic information in a raster format. The delimitation, content and representation of this product are similar to those of 1:50,000 scale topographical maps.  Toporama is published as an edition (or \"release\") approximately every six months. It is available free of charge through the GeoGratis portal (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) in GeoTIFF format, which is a geo-referenced raster format. Toporama is available in the following spatial reference systems: Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) and geographic (latitude and longitude).  Toporama is a product aimed at the general public that can be used by GPS system users who need a geo-referenced raster map product.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018c1f31-1de1-43c9-b4f5-98b1d2f51db3.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "N51d19mW113d10m_6", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "Base de donn\u00e9es des points d'appui au sol, Canada - N51d19mW113d10m_6", "data_series_issue_identification": "N51d19mW113d10m_6", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Base de donn\u00e9es des points d'appui au sol, Canada", "spatial_representation_type": "Image Digital | Image num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "La Base de donn\u00e9es des points d'appui au sol (BDPAS) est une collection d'orthophotographies (ou chips) destin\u00e9e aux utilisateurs de SIG et de t\u00e9l\u00e9d\u00e9tection. La base de donn\u00e9es fournit une information utile et exacte \u00e9tablie \u00e0 partir de photos a\u00e9riennes corrig\u00e9es. L'utilisateur final peut s'y reporter \u00e0 titre de source de donn\u00e9es fondamentales pour corriger et valider les donn\u00e9es satellitaires, vectorielles et matricielles, pour fins de correction et de mise \u00e0 jour des cartes ainsi que d'analyse, de mod\u00e9lisation et de traitement des images. La BDPAS a d'abord \u00e9t\u00e9 constitu\u00e9e pour suppl\u00e9er au traitement et/ou \u00e0 la correction des donn\u00e9es LANDSAT et SPOT afin d'offrir des produits d'imagerie satellitaire \u00e0 valeur ajout\u00e9e. G\u00e9ogratis offre maintenant \u00e0 l'utilisateur final la possibilit\u00e9 d'acc\u00e9der \u00e0 ces donn\u00e9es en ligne de mani\u00e8re efficace et \u00e9conomique.", "presentation_form": "Image Digital | Image num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[51.361359, -113.183368], [51.379824, -113.184247], [51.380375, -113.154526], [51.361909, -113.153659], [51.361359, -113.183368]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Location  Localisation", "tags": [{"name": "Geomatics  G\u00e9omatique"}, {"name": "Geographic data  Donn\u00e9es g\u00e9ographiques"}, {"name": "Photography  Photographie"}, {"name": "Aerial photography  Photographie a\u00e9rienne"}, {"name": "Imagery and Basemaps  Imagerie et carte de base"}, {"name": "GCP  BDPC"}, {"name": "Air photo  Photo a\u00e9rienne"}, {"name": "Ground Control Points  Points dappui au sol"}, {"name": "NTS 82P6  SNRC 82P6"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "1995-05-23", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "Ground Control Database, Canada", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "name": "018c7bd1-a62a-54ce-8604-eacb8983dfcd", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018c7bd1-a62a-54ce-8604-eacb8983dfcd.html", "notes": "The Ground Control Database (GCDB) is a collection of geo-corrected aerial photo images (or chips) developed for the GIS and remote sensing community. The database provides accurate and useful information obtained from corrected aerial photos. This database can be used by the end-user as a fundamental data source for correction and validation of satellite, vector and raster data, as well as for map correcting and updating, analysis, modeling, and image processing. The GCDB was initially developed to supplement processing and/or correction of LANDSAT and SPOT data for value added satellite imagery products. Now, through GeoGratis, online access to the GCDB is offered as an efficient and cost effective method of delivery to the end-user.", "title": "Ground Control Database, Canada - N51d19mW113d10m_6", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018c7bd1-a62a-54ce-8604-eacb8983dfcd.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Les fichiers CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer ont \u00e9t\u00e9 produits \u00e0 partir des cartes topographiques publi\u00e9es par le Gouvernement du Canada. Ces fichiers sont bas\u00e9s sur le Syst\u00e8me national de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence cartographique (SNRC) et disponibles aux \u00e9chelles de 1/50 000 et 1/250 000. Chaque fichier ou jeu de donn\u00e9es CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer contient l'ensemble de l'information figurant au recto de la carte topographique. Cela comprend l'information topographique incluse \u00e0 l'int\u00e9rieur de l'orle cartographique de m\u00eame que l'habillage de la carte, soit l'information situ\u00e9e en p\u00e9riph\u00e9rie de l'orle cartographique.  Les donn\u00e9es contenues dans ce fichier CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer proviennent du balayage d'une carte topographique papier monochrome (noir et blanc).  Suite au balayage initial de la carte papier, ce fichier a \u00e9t\u00e9 inspect\u00e9 et class\u00e9 \" Provisoire\". Ce fichier inclut un filigrane \"Impression provisoire\" au bas du coin inf\u00e9rieur gauche de la carte. La qualit\u00e9 des impressions provisoire varie grandement. Un certain nombre d'op\u00e9rations de nettoyage, d\u00e9coupage, mise \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle et ajustement des tons et couleurs peuvent \u00eatre n\u00e9cessaires afin d'am\u00e9liorer la qualit\u00e9 de l'impression.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-91.5, 62.75], [-91.5, 63], [-91, 63], [-91, 62.75], [-91.5, 62.75]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "CANMATRIX2055J141.0  CANMATRIX2055J141.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "SCARAB POINT  SCARAB POINT"}, {"name": "055J14  055J14"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1965", "data_series_name": "CanMatrix - Print Ready", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1965", "name": "018cde12-4964-4722-a6e1-d436b325b693", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018cde12-4964-4722-a6e1-d436b325b693.html", "notes": "CanMatrix - Print Ready files were produced from topographic maps published by the Government of Canada, and correspond to the National Topographic System (NTS) grid at 1:50 000 and 1:250 000 scales. Each CanMatrix - Print Ready file or dataset contains all of the information shown on the front of the topographic map, including the topographic information within the neatline of the map, and the information in the border of the map outside of the neatline.  This CanMatrix - Print Ready file was produced by scanning a monochrome (black and white) paper topographic map.  Following initial scanning of the paper map, the digital file was inspected and classified as \"Provisional\". This file includes a \"Provisional Print\" watermark in the bottom left corner of the map. The printing quality of Provisional Prints varies greatly. Varying amounts of cleaning, trimming, scaling, and shade/colour adjustment may be required to improve the print quality.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/018cde12-4964-4722-a6e1-d436b325b693.html", "department_number": ""}
