{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Les fichiers CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer ont \u00e9t\u00e9 produits \u00e0 partir des cartes topographiques publi\u00e9es par le Gouvernement du Canada. Ces fichiers sont bas\u00e9s sur le Syst\u00e8me national de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence cartographique (SNRC) et disponibles aux \u00e9chelles de 1/50 000 et 1/250 000. Chaque fichier ou jeu de donn\u00e9es CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer contient l'ensemble de l'information figurant au recto de la carte topographique. Cela comprend l'information topographique incluse \u00e0 l'int\u00e9rieur de l'orle cartographique de m\u00eame que l'habillage de la carte, soit l'information situ\u00e9e en p\u00e9riph\u00e9rie de l'orle cartographique.  Les donn\u00e9es contenues dans ce fichier CanMatrix - Pr\u00eat \u00e0 imprimer proviennent du balayage d'une carte topographique papier monochrome (noir et blanc).  Suite au balayage initial de la carte papier, ce fichier a \u00e9t\u00e9 inspect\u00e9 et class\u00e9 \" Provisoire\". Ce fichier inclut un filigrane \"Impression provisoire\" au bas du coin inf\u00e9rieur gauche de la carte. La qualit\u00e9 des impressions provisoire varie grandement. Un certain nombre d'op\u00e9rations de nettoyage, d\u00e9coupage, mise \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle et ajustement des tons et couleurs peuvent \u00eatre n\u00e9cessaires afin d'am\u00e9liorer la qualit\u00e9 de l'impression.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-109.5, 66.5], [-109.5, 66.75], [-109, 66.75], [-109, 66.5], [-109.5, 66.5]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "CANMATRIX2076K111.0  CANMATRIX2076K111.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "076K11  076K11"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1989", "data_series_name": "CanMatrix - Print Ready", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1989", "name": "01920489-271f-4141-bf84-0ae71d2c47bd", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01920489-271f-4141-bf84-0ae71d2c47bd.html", "notes": "CanMatrix - Print Ready files were produced from topographic maps published by the Government of Canada, and correspond to the National Topographic System (NTS) grid at 1:50 000 and 1:250 000 scales. Each CanMatrix - Print Ready file or dataset contains all of the information shown on the front of the topographic map, including the topographic information within the neatline of the map, and the information in the border of the map outside of the neatline.  This CanMatrix - Print Ready file was produced by scanning a monochrome (black and white) paper topographic map.  Following initial scanning of the paper map, the digital file was inspected and classified as \"Provisional\". This file includes a \"Provisional Print\" watermark in the bottom left corner of the map. The printing quality of Provisional Prints varies greatly. Varying amounts of cleaning, trimming, scaling, and shade/colour adjustment may be required to improve the print quality.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01920489-271f-4141-bf84-0ae71d2c47bd.html", "department_number": ""}
