{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1,1", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1,1", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "CanMatrix - g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "Not Planned | Non planifi\u00e9", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Ce fichier CanMatrix (g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9) est un produit compos\u00e9 de donn\u00e9es matricielles r\u00e9sultant du balayage de la carte papier \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. La source du fichier matriciel (carte papier) est g\u00e9ocod\u00e9e dans le Syst\u00e8me de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence nord-am\u00e9ricain de 1927 (NAD27).  Le fichier matriciel r\u00e9sultant est g\u00e9ocod\u00e9 dans le Syst\u00e8me de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence nord-am\u00e9ricain de 1983 (NAD83) selon la projection Universelle transverse de Mercator (UTM). Le jeu de donn\u00e9es est disponible dans le format G\u00e9oTIFF.  Le Centre d'information topographique d\u00e9sire mettre en place l'\u00e9quivalent d'une base de donn\u00e9es nationale continue de cartes matricielles o\u00f9 chaque pixel poss\u00e8de une situation g\u00e9ographique distincte.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-72.25, 61.5], [-72.25, 61.75], [-72, 61.75], [-72, 61.5], [-72.25, 61.5]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "CANMATRIX035H09_E1.0  CANMATRIX035H09_E1.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "MONT ALBERT-LOW  MONT ALBERT-LOW"}, {"name": "035H09_E  035H09_E"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1958", "data_series_name": "CanMatrix - georeferenced", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1958", "name": "01958871-ee12-48dd-872e-350832a3b7ac", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01958871-ee12-48dd-872e-350832a3b7ac.html", "notes": "This CanMatrix (georeferenced) file is composed of raster data from the scanned map at the 1:50 000 scale. The source of this raster file (paper map) is geocoded according to the North American Datum of 1927 (NAD27).  The resulting raster file is georeferenced to the North American Datum of 1983 (NAD 83) according to the Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) projection. This product is distributed in GeoTIFF.  The Centre for Topographic Information wants to create a national database composed of raster map data where each pixel has a distinct geographic location (georeferenced data).", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/01958871-ee12-48dd-872e-350832a3b7ac.html", "department_number": ""}
