ocalisation", "tags": [{"name": "Geomatics  G\u00e9omatique"}, {"name": "Geographic data  Donn\u00e9es g\u00e9ographiques"}, {"name": "Photography  Photographie"}, {"name": "Aerial photography  Photographie a\u00e9rienne"}, {"name": "Imagery and Basemaps  Imagerie et carte de base"}, {"name": "GCP  BDPC"}, {"name": "Air photo  Photo a\u00e9rienne"}, {"name": "Ground Control Points  Points dappui au sol"}, {"name": "NTS 105J15  SNRC 105J15"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "1977-08-05", "time_period_coverage_start": "", "data_series_name": "Ground Control Database, Canada", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "", "name": "019a33d1-fae2-5887-af17-7af012f20ce0", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019a33d1-fae2-5887-af17-7af012f20ce0.html", "notes": "The Ground Control Database (GCDB) is a collection of geo-corrected aerial photo images (or chips) developed for the GIS and remote sensing community. The database provides accurate and useful information obtained from corrected aerial photos. This database can be used by the end-user as a fundamental data source for correction and validation of satellite, vector and raster data, as well as for map correcting and updating, analysis, modeling, and image processing. The GCDB was initially developed to supplement processing and/or correction of LANDSAT and SPOT data for value added satellite imagery products. Now, through GeoGratis, online access to the GCDB is offered as an efficient and cost effective method of delivery to the end-user.", "title": "Ground Control Database, Canada - N62d52mW130d41m_2", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019a33d1-fae2-5887-af17-7af012f20ce0.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Toporama", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "Biannually | Semestriel", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Toporama est un produit num\u00e9rique de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence topographique produit par Ressources naturelles Canada (RNCan). Toporama couvre le territoire canadien et offre une information topographique, g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9e et symbolis\u00e9e en format matriciel. Le d\u00e9coupage, le contenu et la repr\u00e9sentation de ce produit sont similaires \u00e0 celui des cartes topographiques \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle 1/50 000.  Toporama est publi\u00e9 sous forme d'\u00e9dition (\u00ab release \u00bb) selon un intervalle d'environ six mois. Toporama est distribu\u00e9 sans frais par l'entremise du portail G\u00e9oGratis (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) dans le format matriciel GeoTIFF qui est un format matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9. Toporama est disponible dans les syst\u00e8mes de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatial suivants : universel transverse de Mercator (UTM) et g\u00e9ographique (latitude et longitude).  Toporama est un produit destin\u00e9 au grand public pouvant \u00eatre utilis\u00e9 notamment par les utilisateurs de syst\u00e8mes GPS qui ont besoin d'un produit cartographique matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-133, 57.75], [-133, 58], [-132.5, 58], [-132.5, 57.75], [-133, 57.75]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "TOPORAMA104F155.0  TOPORAMA104F155.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Science Keywords BIOSPHERE VEGETATION  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques biosph\u00e8re v\u00e9g\u00e9tation"}, {"name": "Administratives Boundaries  Limites administratives"}, {"name": "Buildings and Structures  B\u00e2timents et structures"}, {"name": "Energy  \u00c9nergie"}, {"name": "Hydrography  Hydrographie"}, {"name": "Industrial and Commercial Areas  Zones industrielles et commerciales"}, {"name": "Places of Interest  Lieux dint\u00e9r\u00eats"}, {"name": "Relief and Landforms  Relief et formes"}, {"name": "ToponymyPlace Names  ToponymieNoms de lieux"}, {"name": "Water Saturated Soils  Sols satur\u00e9s deau"}, {"name": "OWENS PEAK  OWENS PEAK"}, {"name": "104F15  104F15"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1974", "data_series_name": "Toporama", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1974", "name": "019a6b2b-e5fd-4cde-9c5a-e6abfd56ee15", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019a6b2b-e5fd-4cde-9c5a-e6abfd56ee15.html", "notes": "Toporama is a digital topographic reference product developed by Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). It covers the entire area of Canada's landmass and provides topographic, geo-referenced, and symbolic information in a raster format. The delimitation, content and representation of this product are similar to those of 1:50,000 scale topographical maps.  Toporama is published as an edition (or \"release\") approximately every six months. It is available free of charge through the GeoGratis portal (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) in GeoTIFF format, which is a geo-referenced raster format. Toporama is available in the following spatial reference systems: Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) and geographic (latitude and longitude).  Toporama is a product aimed at the general public that can be used by GPS system users who need a geo-referenced raster map product.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019a6b2b-e5fd-4cde-9c5a-e6abfd56ee15.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Donn\u00e9es num\u00e9riques d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation du Canada", "spatial_representation_type": "Model Digital | Mod\u00e8le num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Le Centre d'information topographique (CIT) produit les DNEC de concert avec des organismes f\u00e9d\u00e9raux, provinciaux et territoriaux ainsi qu'avec le secteur priv\u00e9.   Les DNEC consistent en un tableau ordonn\u00e9 de valeurs d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation au sol ou de surface (enregistr\u00e9es en m\u00e8tres) interpol\u00e9es \u00e0 des points r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement espac\u00e9s. Les donn\u00e9es sources num\u00e9riques des DNEC peuvent \u00eatre extraites des \u00e9l\u00e9ments hypsographiques et hydrographiques de la Base nationale de donn\u00e9es topographiques (BNDT) aux \u00e9chelles de 1/50 000 et 1/250 000, ou de la Base de donn\u00e9es g\u00e9ospatiales (BDG), ou de donn\u00e9es de position, \u00e0 diverses \u00e9chelles, acquises des provinces et territoires ou d'imageries de t\u00e9l\u00e9d\u00e9tection.", "presentation_form": "Model Digital | Mod\u00e8le num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-102.5, 55], [-102.5, 55.25], [-102, 55.25], [-102, 55], [-102.5, 55]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Elevation  \u00c9l\u00e9vation", "tags": [{"name": "CDED063M011.0  DNEC063M011.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "063M01  063M01"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1966", "data_series_name": "Canadian Digital Elevation Data", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1966", "name": "019a8e2a-008d-4571-a078-458d191c8370", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019a8e2a-008d-4571-a078-458d191c8370.html", "notes": "The Centre for Topographic Information (CTI) jointly produces the CDED with federal, provincial and territorial government agencies as well as the private sector.   A CDED consists of an ordered array of ground or reflective surface elevations, recorded in metres, at regularly spaced intervals. The source digital data for CDED is extracted from the hypsographic and hydrographic elements of the National Topographic Data Base (NTDB) at scales of 1:50,000 and 1:250,000, or the Geospatial Data Base (GDB), or various scaled positional data acquired by the provinces and territories, or remotely sensed imagery.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019a8e2a-008d-4571-a078-458d191c8370.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "2.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "2.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Matrices de correction de la BNDT", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "Not Planned | Non planifi\u00e9", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Les matrices de correction de la Base nationale de donn\u00e9es topographiques (BNDT), aussi connu sous l'acronyme MATCOR, sont un produit d\u00e9riv\u00e9 du rehaussement planim\u00e9trique des jeux de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. La matrice de correction permet \u00e0 l'utilisateur d'am\u00e9liorer la pr\u00e9cision g\u00e9om\u00e9trique des donn\u00e9es moins pr\u00e9cises de la BNDT. La matrice est un ensemble de points r\u00e9partis sur une grille r\u00e9guli\u00e8re aux 100 m\u00e8tres, chaque point d\u00e9crivant les corrections planim\u00e9triques (DX, DY) \u00e0 apporter \u00e0 cet endroit. La position des points est en coordonn\u00e9es UTM (projection universelle transverse de Mercator) selon le syst\u00e8me de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence nord-am\u00e9ricain de 1983 (NAD83). Chaque fichier forme une zone rectangulaire recouvrant en son entier le jeu de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT associ\u00e9. Son d\u00e9coupage correspond donc grossi\u00e8rement au Syst\u00e8me national de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence cartographique (SNRC) \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000. Tous les jeux de donn\u00e9es de la BNDT \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle de 1/50 000, dont la pr\u00e9cision originale est inf\u00e9rieure \u00e0 30 m\u00e8tres, devraient \u00eatre corrig\u00e9s g\u00e9om\u00e9triquement en utilisant des ortho-images Landsat comme r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatiale. Le jeu de donn\u00e9es MATCOR contient une liste de coordonn\u00e9es et les corrections correspondantes \u00e0 appliquer sous la forme : X Y DX DY.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-69.5, 52.5], [-69.5, 52.75], [-69, 52.75], [-69, 52.5], [-69.5, 52.5]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "MAT-CORR-BNDT-L7023C112.3  MAT-CORR-BNDT-L7023C112.3"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Science Keywords HYDROSPHERE SURFACE WATER  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques hydrosph\u00e8re eau de surface"}, {"name": "Science Keywords LAND SURFACE TOPOGRAPHY  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques surface terrestre topographie"}, {"name": "Science Keywords BIOSPHERE VEGETATION  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques biosph\u00e8re v\u00e9g\u00e9tation"}, {"name": "LAC DESPINOLLES  LAC DESPINOLLES"}, {"name": "023C11  023C11"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "2001-05-23", "data_series_name": "NTDB Correction Matrices", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "2001-05-23", "name": "019aa9e6-a2e4-44f5-9014-9880e0485f6d", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019aa9e6-a2e4-44f5-9014-9880e0485f6d.html", "notes": "The correction matrices for the National Topographic Data Base (NTDB), also known under the acronym CORMAT, are products derived from the planimetric enhancement of NTDB data sets at the 1:50 000 scale. The correction matrix enables users to enhance the geometric accuracy of the less accurate NTDB. The matrix is a set of points arrayed on a regular 100-m grid. Each point describes the planimetric correction (DX, DY) to be applied at this location. The position of the points is given in UTM (Universal Transverse Mercator projection) coordinates based on the North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83). Each file constitutes a rectangular area covering the entire corresponding NTDB data set. Its delimitation corresponds more or less to National Topographic System (NTS) divisions at the 1:50 000 scale. All NTDB data sets at the 1:50 000 scale whose original accuracy was less than 30 m should be geometrically corrected by using the Landsat orthoimage as a spatial reference. A CORMAT data set contains a list of coordinates and the corresponding corrections to be applied in the form X Y DX DY.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019aa9e6-a2e4-44f5-9014-9880e0485f6d.html", "department_number": ""}
