{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "1.0", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "1.0", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Toporama", "spatial_representation_type": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "Biannually | Semestriel", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Toporama est un produit num\u00e9rique de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence topographique produit par Ressources naturelles Canada (RNCan). Toporama couvre le territoire canadien et offre une information topographique, g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9e et symbolis\u00e9e en format matriciel. Le d\u00e9coupage, le contenu et la repr\u00e9sentation de ce produit sont similaires \u00e0 celui des cartes topographiques \u00e0 l'\u00e9chelle 1/50 000.  Toporama est publi\u00e9 sous forme d'\u00e9dition (\u00ab release \u00bb) selon un intervalle d'environ six mois. Toporama est distribu\u00e9 sans frais par l'entremise du portail G\u00e9oGratis (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) dans le format matriciel GeoTIFF qui est un format matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9. Toporama est disponible dans les syst\u00e8mes de r\u00e9f\u00e9rence spatial suivants : universel transverse de Mercator (UTM) et g\u00e9ographique (latitude et longitude).  Toporama est un produit destin\u00e9 au grand public pouvant \u00eatre utilis\u00e9 notamment par les utilisateurs de syst\u00e8mes GPS qui ont besoin d'un produit cartographique matriciel g\u00e9or\u00e9f\u00e9renc\u00e9.", "presentation_form": "Map Digital | Carte num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-122, 68.75], [-122, 69], [-121, 69], [-121, 68.75], [-122, 68.75]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Imagery Base Maps Earth Cover  Imagerie carte de base couverture terrestre", "tags": [{"name": "TOPORAMA097A154.0  TOPORAMA097A154.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "Sciences de la Terre  Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques aspects humains infrastructure b\u00e2timents"}, {"name": "Science Keywords TERRESTRIAL HYDROSPHERE SURFACE WATER WETLANDS  B\u00e2timents et structures"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques aspects humains infrastructure b\u00e2timents  \u00c9nergie"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques aspects humains infrastructure communications  Hydrographie"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques aspects humains infrastructure entit\u00e9s culturelles  Lieux dint\u00e9r\u00eats"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques aspects humains infrastructure \u00e9lectricit\u00e9  Relief et formes"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques surface terrestre topographie altitude du relief  ToponymieNoms de lieux"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques surface terrestre utilisationcouverture des terres  Sols satur\u00e9s deau"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques aspects humains infrastructure pipelines  097A15Nunavut"}, {"name": "Mots-cl\u00e9s scientifiques surface terrestre topographie relief topographique  097A15"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1974", "data_series_name": "Toporama", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1974", "name": "019df850-afa6-49ca-bb21-cf5bfd9d7d68", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019df850-afa6-49ca-bb21-cf5bfd9d7d68.html", "notes": "Toporama is a digital topographic reference product developed by Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). It covers the entire area of Canada's landmass and provides topographic, geo-referenced, and symbolic information in a raster format. The delimitation, content and representation of this product are similar to those of 1:50,000 scale topographical maps.  Toporama is published as an edition (or \"release\") approximately every six months. It is available free of charge through the GeoGratis portal (www.GeoGratis.gc.ca) in GeoTIFF format, which is a geo-referenced raster format. Toporama is available in the following spatial reference systems: Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM) and geographic (latitude and longitude).  Toporama is a product aimed at the general public that can be used by GPS system users who need a geo-referenced raster map product.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019df850-afa6-49ca-bb21-cf5bfd9d7d68.html", "department_number": ""}
{"data_series_issue_identification_fra": "GEOBASE_2.1", "catalog_type": "Geo Data | G\\u00e9o", "title_fra": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "data_series_issue_identification": "GEOBASE_2.1", "ready_to_publish": "0", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "", "data_series_name_fra": "Donn\u00e9es num\u00e9riques d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation du Canada", "spatial_representation_type": "Model Digital | Mod\u00e8le num\u00e9rique", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "As Needed | Au besoin", "author": "Natural Resources Canada | Ressources naturelles Canada", "author_email": "", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Le Centre d'information topographique (CIT) produit les DNEC de concert avec des organismes f\u00e9d\u00e9raux, provinciaux et territoriaux ainsi qu'avec le secteur priv\u00e9.   Les DNEC consistent en un tableau ordonn\u00e9 de valeurs d'\u00e9l\u00e9vation au sol ou de surface (enregistr\u00e9es en m\u00e8tres) interpol\u00e9es \u00e0 des points r\u00e9guli\u00e8rement espac\u00e9s. Les donn\u00e9es sources num\u00e9riques des DNEC peuvent \u00eatre extraites des \u00e9l\u00e9ments hypsographiques et hydrographiques de la Base nationale de donn\u00e9es topographiques (BNDT) aux \u00e9chelles de 1/50 000 et 1/250 000, ou de la Base de donn\u00e9es g\u00e9ospatiales (BDG), ou de donn\u00e9es de position, \u00e0 diverses \u00e9chelles, acquises des provinces et territoires ou d'imageries de t\u00e9l\u00e9d\u00e9tection.", "presentation_form": "Model Digital | Mod\u00e8le num\u00e9rique", "spatial": "{\"type\": \"Polygon\", \"coordinates\": [[[-83.5, 64.25], [-83.5, 64.5], [-83, 64.5], [-83, 64.25], [-83.5, 64.25]]]}", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "Elevation  \u00c9l\u00e9vation", "tags": [{"name": "CDED046B061.0  DNEC046B061.0"}, {"name": "Earth Science  Sciences de la Terre"}, {"name": "046B06  046B06"}], "endpoint_url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "date_published": "2010-11-02", "time_period_coverage_start": "1978", "data_series_name": "Canadian Digital Elevation Data", "endpoint_url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/", "time_period_coverage_end": "1978", "name": "019edb61-623c-4d0a-80ca-8b1d37ddb6b7", "language": "", "url": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/en/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019edb61-623c-4d0a-80ca-8b1d37ddb6b7.html", "notes": "The Centre for Topographic Information (CTI) jointly produces the CDED with federal, provincial and territorial government agencies as well as the private sector.   A CDED consists of an ordered array of ground or reflective surface elevations, recorded in metres, at regularly spaced intervals. The source digital data for CDED is extracted from the hypsographic and hydrographic elements of the National Topographic Data Base (NTDB) at scales of 1:50,000 and 1:250,000, or the Geospatial Data Base (GDB), or various scaled positional data acquired by the provinces and territories, or remotely sensed imagery.", "title": "EPSG Geodetic Parameter Registry", "url_fra": "http://geogratis.gc.ca/api/fr/nrcan-rncan/ess-sst/019edb61-623c-4d0a-80ca-8b1d37ddb6b7.html", "department_number": ""}
